  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "YVFFahh4bm4FccQ4lvZu+Cq9XV0=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:26.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "# actions become operations after dispatch adding metadata\n\nThe distinction between actions and operations is fundamental to the Powerhouse document model:\n\n- **Action** \u2014 A proposed change. A JSON object with `type` (action name) and `input` (payload). This is what you dispatch.\n- **Operation** \u2014 A completed change. Contains the original action plus system metadata: `index`, `timestamp`, `hash`, and optional `error`.\n\nActions become operations after dispatch through `addActions`. The system appends metadata that enables event sourcing \u2014 the index provides ordering, the hash enables integrity verification, and the timestamp records when it happened.\n\nSince [[operation errors are recorded on operations not thrown to callers]], even failed actions produce operations (with the error captured in the `error` field).\n\n---\n\nTopics:\n- [[architecture decisions]]\n- [[reducer patterns]]",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:26.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:26.000Z"
    }
  },
